<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> custom element groups a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a>/<a href="/docs/elements/native/dd/"><code>&lt;dd&gt;</code></a> pair within a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> for styling. Apply class variants on the parent <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> to get built-in layouts — no custom CSS needed.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variants</h2>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Class</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.horizontal</code></td>
          <td>Side-by-side key-value rows (grid layout)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.stacked</code></td>
          <td>Label above value (flex column)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.bordered</code></td>
          <td>Separator lines between items</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>.compact</code></td>
          <td>Tight spacing for dense data</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-striped</code></td>
          <td>Alternating row backgrounds</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Variants compose freely — combine <code>.horizontal</code>, <code>.bordered</code>, and <code>.compact</code> on a single <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Horizontal</h2>
    <p>Side-by-side key-value pairs. Combine with <code>.bordered</code> for separator lines between rows.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-item-horizontal.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/dl-item/horizontal"
      title="Horizontal dl-item"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Horizontal + bordered">{{ horizontalCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Stacked</h2>
    <p>Label above value with muted term styling. Good for metadata or profile fields.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-item-stacked.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/dl-item/stacked"
      title="Stacked dl-item"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Stacked layout">{{ stackedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Compact</h2>
    <p>Tighter spacing for dense data. Combine with <code>.horizontal</code> and <code>.bordered</code>.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-item-compact.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/dl-item/compact"
      title="Compact dl-item"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Compact + horizontal + bordered">{{ compactCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Striped</h2>
    <p>Alternating row backgrounds using the <code>data-striped</code> attribute — the same attribute used on plain <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> elements.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-item-striped.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/dl-item/striped"
      title="Striped dl-item"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Striped + horizontal">{{ stripedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multiple Values</h2>
    <p>A single <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> can hold one <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> with multiple <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-item-multiple.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/dl-item/multiple"
      title="Multiple values"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Multiple values">{{ multipleValuesCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why a Custom Element?</h2>
    <p>HTML5 allows wrapping <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pairs in <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>, but <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> is more specific than <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> in both CSS selectors and code readability. It describes its purpose — grouping a description list item — without carrying the ambiguity of a generic container.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Model</h2>

    <h3>Permitted Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>One or more <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements</li>
      <li>One or more <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements</li>
      <li>The <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements should come before <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Required Parent</h3>
    <p>Must be a direct child of <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> — Description list container (required parent)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a> — Definition term (the key/label)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dd/"><code>&lt;dd&gt;</code></a> — Definition description (the value)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
